What’s the #1 thing you took away from this so far?
Is there anything that you found to be really cool?

I think something it's gotten me to do is look at a problem in a bunch of different ways. Like i'll start a problem and do it an easy way right off the bat, and realize that I'm not gunna be able to just brute force it, so I have to try and come up with another unique way to solve it, and then in doing so you think of a few other ways you could solve it. Then you start to realize that for some of the problems your initial way to solve it isn't just the easy brute force way anymore, but rather you're starting to immediately go towards the more complex/efficient way of solving it.
That is actually really good insight! I completely agree.

I was going to say the checking if a large number is prime trick is really cool. But our thoughts go hand in hand in a way. Because I learned that new trick, I won’t ever think of brute forcing checking prime numbers ever again.
Whenever I see “Prime Number” I always start by writing out the neat function that checks primes efficiently.
